III. Details of Special Diagnostic Processing 


1. Overview of ECU Reprogramming (SPS)


1-1           What is iSPS (Interface Service Programming System)?

Most of information of ECU SPS data is stored in the PC (GMDAT Loader Installed), because SCAN-100 cannot store all SPS data in the memory card due to the limited space for lots of ECU SPS variant data. To reprogram of new ECU software data into an ECU on vehicle, it is required to interface with PC for gathering of the proper ECU SPS data files. So, it is called as 'iSPS'.

 

1-2           ECU Program Memory

There are three kind of program memory in the ECU

 

A.     Boot Software: ECU booting

B.      Operation/Application Software: An algorism of system controls

C.     Calibration: Optimized values for each system option

 

Generally, among above memories, ECU Reprogramming will program the part of operation software and calibration. But, for Diesel ECU are programmed with boot software.

 

1-3           SPS Data

Generally, SPS Data is ECU software files (operation software and calibrations). In addition, all information for ECU reprogramming will be called as SPS data.

 

A.     ECU data files: Software and Calibration Data as a binary format

B.      Master Parts List (MPL): a part number list of ECU data files

C.     Vehicle Built Data: Vehicle built history at production line like that ECU hardware or software programmed a specific vehicle.

 

For the ECU reprogramming of C100 vehicle, all SPS data must be stored in the 'GMDAT Loader' in the PC. These SPS data will be delivered on every update.

 

1-4           Master Part List

All ECU has a software part number based on each ECU specific module requirements. It is possible to reprogram an ECU when all module data is combined correctly.

 

A. Utility File: This is not memory for ECU. It is a programming utility for ECU reprogramming. All ECU's have a specific utility file. Normally, the module ID number is '00'.

-> Module ID: 00

 

B.   Operation Software: This is major memory with the largest one among total ECU memory size. Based on ECU feature, there is one or more software modules.

->  Module ID: 01 (If more than 2, the module number will be assigned '02' and '03')

2. SCAN-100 R-card Application

 

The Diesel ECM's SPS data of C100 is the biggest memory size among overall GMDAT vehicle ECU. To store C100 Diesel ECM SPS data, the Reprogramming R-card needs 2.3 M Bytes as a minimum.

 

2-1 4 MB R-card

The 4 MB R-card can be stored one kind of ECU SPS data.

 

1)     SPS Data Download using by iSPS (for C100 ECU only)

Using the iSPS function, one ECU SPS data from PC can be downloaded into R-card. Using this function, new SPS data will be overwritten whenever a SPS data already exist or not in R-card.

 

2)     SPS Data Download using KWP Send (for all vehicles including V250/C100)

Using this KWP Send function, one DWN file from PC can be downloaded into R-card. If a DWN data already exist in R-card, this DWN file can be downloaded after deleting of exiting DWN file in R-card. SCAN-100 download mode is '4] Data Record (PC => SCAN-100)'.

 

2-2 16 MB R-card

The 16 MB R-card can be stored seven kinds of ECU SPS data at a same time.

Memory Position

Files by iSPS or KWP Send

1

iSPS or KWP Send 1

2

KWP Send 2

3

KWP Send 3

4

KWP Send 4

5

KWP Send 5

6

KWP Send 6

7

KWP Send 7

 

1)     SPS Data Download using by iSPS (for C100 ECU only)

Using the iSPS function, one ECU SPS data from PC can be downloaded into R-card #1 position only. Using this function, new SPS data will be overwritten whenever a SPS data already exist or not in R-card #1 position.

 

2)     SPS Data Download using KWP Send (for all vehicles including V250/C100)

Using this KWP Send function, 7 DWN files from PC can be downloaded into R-card. If 7 DWN data already exist in R-card, a new DWN file can be downloaded after deleting of one (at least) exiting DWN file in R-card. SCAN-100 download mode is '4] Multi-Data Record(PC => SCAN-100)'.

4. Security Access (SA)

 

To avoid unauthorized manipulation ( reading / erasing / writing actions ) of the ECU data, security accesses are implemented to allow / forbid access to the content of the flash EPROM. A SEED ( random value ) is sent by the ECU to the tool. The same algorithm within the tool and the ECU allows to provide a KEY. The ECU authorizes the access to the security level if the key processed by the tester matches with the ECU's KEY.

 

Key value = function (Seed )

 

 

[Procedure of Security Access]

If security access is required during some ECU's diagnostic, SCAN-100 displays " Please Run to Security Access and then this security access is required."

 

[Summary of diagnostic item needed by security access]

1)      ECU Reprogramming. During the ECU reprogramming procedure, this security access will be performed internally between SCAN-100 and an ECU. So, it is not required to run separated 'security access' function.

2)      'ECM Immobilizer Learning' for diesel ECM (Engine Control Module).

3)      'Wheel Circumference', 'Vehicle Variant Coding' and 'Injector IQA Coding' for Diesel ECM (Engine Control Module).

4)      'Key Learning' for VTD (vehicle theft Deterrent).

7. Recommended Procedure if needs ECU replacement

 

Diesel ECM

1)      Before ECM replacement

a.      If possible to communicate with old ECM, using by 'A-9', backup existing data in old ECM. If not possible, change ECM at once.

2)      After ECM replacement

a.      ECM Reprogramming (SPS)

b.      If SCAN-100 has backup data from the old ECM, perform 'A-9 [Backup Programming]' to write the backup data into new ECM. And set of the initialization of A-2, A-3, A-4.

c.      If SCAN-100 has no backup data from old ECM, (because new ECM does not know current oil life) change engine oil and perform 'A-1'. And perform of A-2, A-3, A-4, A-5, A-6, A-7 and A-8.

d.      Using 'A-10', perform ECM Immobilizer Learning.

 

Gasoline 2.4L ECM : After ECM replacement

a.      ECM Reprogramming (SPS)

b.      Using B-1, B-2, B-3 and B-4, perform the initialization or programming.

c.      Like 'A-10', perform ECM Immobilizer Learning.

(Note: It must be required to use the menu located in 2.4L ECM)

 

Gasoline 3.2L ECM : After ECM replacement

a.      ECM Reprogramming (SPS)

b.      Using C-1 and C-2, perform the initialization or programming.

c.      Like 'A-10', perform ECM Immobilizer Learning.

(Note: It must be required to use the menu located in 3.2L ECM)

 

TCM :  After TCM replacement

a.      TCM Reprogramming (SPS)

b.      Using 'D-1', reset the learned values

 

EBCM :  After EBCM replacement

a.      EBCM Reprogramming (SPS)

b.   If a car has ESP option, using 'E-1' set the steering angle sensor of zero position.

Note: These files are located in the source data files of the TIS DVD and can be located using windows explorer.

Files delivered in the TIS-DVD/CD;

:\GMDSCAN_V.VV.VV.YYMMDD_EN_SETUP_YYYYMMDD_HH.MM.bat

:\GMDAT Loader \ GMDSCAN_V.VV.VV.YYMMDD_EN_SETUP_YYYYMMDD_HH.MM.exe

( GMDSCAN_V.VV.VV.YYMMDD_EN_SETUP_YYYYMMDD_HH.MM.bat)
